For a step-up chopper, the output voltage \( V_o \) is related to the input voltage \( V_s \) and duty cycle \( D \) by \( V_o = \frac{V_s}{1-D} \).  
Given \( V_s = 110 \, \text{V} \) and \( V_o = 150 \, \text{V} \), we solve \( 150 = \frac{110}{1-D} \) to get \( 1-D = \frac{110}{150} = 0.7333 \), so \( D = 0.2667 \approx 0.27 \).  

